<head>HOST</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>PARTY-GIVER</item>
<item>HOSTESS</item>
<item>ENTERTAINER</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">主人</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>LEADER of a HOME OR FEAST.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for the host on a ritual occasion is zhǔ 主</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>主人</p>
<p>主</p>
<p>東家</p>
<p>東道</p>
<p>東 is limited to idiomatic phrases.</p>
<p>作東 is a formal way of referring to playing the host.</p>
<p>東人</p>
<p>地主</p>
<p>主人公</p>
<p>家主</p>
<p>家公</p>
<p>主婦 refers to the hostess.</p>
<p>主母 refers to the hostess.</p>
<p/>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
